<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Fashion designer Pip Edwards boasts a social media following of more than 165,000 on Instagram.</p>

<p>And on Wednesday, the P.E Nation founder used her star power to shed light and help raise money for a child with rare type of cancer.</p>

<p>The 40-year-old shared a photo of the little girl with her family, along with the caption: 'My heart goes out to Lani Webb and her darling daughter Arlowe.'</p>

<p>'No parent ever wants to go through this': On Wednesday, Pip Edwards (pictured) used her star power to help raise money for a child diagnosed with a rare type of cancer</p>

<p>She continued: 'Arlowe is 20-months-old and last week she was diagnosed with a rare type of cancer called Ewing Sarcoma.'</p>

<p>Ewing Sarcoma is a rare cancer that occurs most often in the bones of the trunk (pelvis, scapula, and ribs) or long bones, such as the femur, according to The Royal Children's Hospital Melbourne.</p>

<p>At the end of her post, Pip urged her followers to: 'Help us raise money to help this beautiful little girl and her family.'</p>

<p>Support: The 40-year-old shared a photo of the little girl with her family, along with the caption: 'My heart goes out to Lani Webb and her darling daughter Arlowe'</p>

